Indien je graag gebruik maakt van onze MTBs, laat dit zeker tijdig weten. Indien er nog vragen zijn, kan je altijd bij mij terecht. We kijken er alvast naar uit om jullie aan de start te verwelkomen! Hi Filip, Thank you for confirming your ability to complete this process by September First, Im glad to share that we were able to get the approval we needed to honor DPG Medias historical Net- payment terms with Dataiku. This change will be reflected in the final executable version of our paperworkRegarding the outstanding PO and payment, given the quick timeframe to finalize this process, our finance team came up with a creative solution that will hopefully remove friction from the process for both sides. Weve simply amended the invoice language of the Order Form to the following: Dataiku will issue the credit memo for the , and an invoice for , upon execution of this Order. Dataiku will apply the Credit against any Outstanding Amounts. Following this, the Customer shall then notify Dataiku how it wishes the remaining credit amount to be applied to the above invoicesBasically this means that upon execution, Dataiku will be able to immediately invoice DPG for the outstanding . balance. However, no payment will be due because we will simply apply the credit from the new contract. So effectively, without your team having to take any action, well take care of the outstanding payment issues and your team will simply need to tell us how they would like us to apply the remaining . credit to the year and year invoices for the new subscription termThis helps us because it means we can immediately recognize this revenue in the year it was booked without having to wait for your team to issue the missing POAnd hopefully it helps you because it means your team doesnt have to scramble to generate a PO on short notice and can simply issue one single PO for the new contract amountAs soon as youre able to help us finalize the user count tomorrow, we should be in a good position to get you executable paperwork within a business day or so.
